KROPOTKIN PRINCIPLES
1. Small is Beautiful.
2. We Build Strength Through Diversity.
3. There is Plenty for Everyone.
4. Co-Operation is the Natural State.
5. Machines are the Best Drudges.

KROPOTKIN PRACTISES
A. We limit code to at most 100 lines (in any language). [Principle 1]
B. We limit side effects to specialist code (for database changes, external messages, and so on). [Principle 1]
C. We allow multiple handlers for the same messages (using Resolvers). [Principles 2 and 4]
D. All communication is via messaging. [Principles 3 and 4]
E. All messages are public and may be received by any process. [Principle 4]
F. We only create and read data, never update or delete it. [Principles 1 and 3]
G. We require thorough tests and comprehensive monitors for all components. [Principle 5]
H. We deploy changes when they pass all tests. [Principles 3 and 5]
I. Processes may run in any reasonable language. [Principle 2]

